>complexity (hence cost) of a network is a barrier for implementation.

The cost of being the source of a DDoS, or having your customer me the 
source of a DDoS doesn't factor in to this equation. It could be argued 
that at present such costs are borne by the victim of the DDoS.

I've resigned myself to the expectation that this mentality will prevail in 
many areas until a victim successfully sues a network operator and end user 
who fail to implement BCP 38, and thus through negligence contribute to the 
damage to a victim.


